<item>
            <title>[LU-19337] conf-sanity/32 takes very long awaiting for devices to go</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19337</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;t32_wait_til_devices_gone() lists devices using do_rpc_nodes $node $LCTL device_list,&lt;br/&gt;
the do_rpc_nodes includes test-framework.sh which does:&lt;br/&gt;
if [ -f &quot;$EXCEPT_LIST_FILE&quot; ]; then&lt;br/&gt;
       echo &quot;Reading test skip list from $EXCEPT_LIST_FILE&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
       cat $EXCEPT_LIST_FILE&lt;br/&gt;
       . $EXCEPT_LIST_FILE&lt;br/&gt;
fi&lt;br/&gt;
i.e. it prints EXCEPT_LIST_FILE and t32_wait_til_devices_gone() interprets that as still alive devices&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
